- "rating 'A'" represents the highest rating a school can receive, indicating exceptional performance;
- "gold star of excellence" is a metaphor for the highest rating, symbolizing outstanding achievement.

sql:
SELECT rating
FROM performance_ratings
WHERE year = 2019;

SELECT COUNT(principal_id) AS total_principals
FROM principals
WHERE district_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS plan_count
FROM improvement_plans
WHERE year = 2019;

